website_engagment_text: More focus on student and faculty accomplishments
comments: Printed issues are expensive to produce and mail.  Save money by using electronic versions

most_info_text: I don't need information about GVSU

comments: I like receiving the magazine in the mail! It's more exciting to receive and read than just another email or link. Everything is digital now, so it's nice to have a real object in front of me to look through. I also share the magazine with my parents for them to read.

most_info_text: This is the first I knew that there was such a publication
website_engagment_text: change the behavior of your students
comments: I have been told by many locals that GVSU students spent the entire GVSU/FSU game chanting "FU, Ferris." Why would I want to be associated with your university?
I really enjoyed this months article "Water in the West".  Living in Las Vegas is so different than Michigan.  It's great the group of students got to experience what we live with daily.

I only receive the GVM through email because I have a current student at GVSU.  I don't tend to read the articles unless something particularly interesting to me is in the headlines, or it is something that applies to current students.
The pictures associated with the articles are amazing!
I answered "neutral" on questions about the printed magazine as I no longer receive it.  The printed magazine is very high quality.  But the on line version can be read anywhere, anytime.
No more printed issues of the magazine.

most_info_text: GV Now - daily email (I'm a staff member and alum)
comments: I haven't read much on the website since the email shifted to being only headers and links to the website. I personally liked it more when the email had some content so I could get a brief overview. I'm not going to click on each link so I can read two sentences about each item...
This is a great survey, allowed me to answer honestly without feeling pressured to answer a certain way.

website_engagment_text: I'm not sure there is anything that you can do to make me more interested in the website. When so much media is digital these days, I really like having the print version arrive at my home for me to leaf through and get off a screen for once. Because I enjoy that experience I just don't feel as compelled to visit the virtual publication and would likely just not read any of it if it was only available digitally.

comments: I would like to see articles in some of the lesser known majors and departments.
Most of my reading of the magazine is through emailed links. I typically do not browse the website or visit it for reading. I would prefer a printed copy but don't believe I am getting them mailed.
I love when important dates are recapped. Helps me keep track.
